    "examples": [
      {
        "example": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Example:",
            "spans": []
          },
          {
            "type": "preformatted",
            "text": "The law requires everyone to follow the speed limit and other traffic regulations, but in Suffolk County, exceptions should be made for cops and their families, police union officials say.\n\nPolice Benevolent Association president Jeff Frayler said Thursday it has been union policy to discourage Suffolk police officers from issuing tickets to fellow officers, regardless of where they work.\n\n\"Police officers have discretion whenever they stop anyone, but they should particularly extend that courtesy in the case of other police officers and their families,\" Frayler said in a brief telephone interview Thursday. \"It is a professional courtesy.\"",
            "spans": []
          }
        ]
